These rules apply to a Bun + Svelte frontend with many routes.
They enforce clean architecture, strict naming, and production-safe error handling.

## Global Rules (All Files)

### Naming Conventions (Strict)

Files & folders:
- kebab-case
- Examples:
  - user-profile.ts
  - auth-store.ts
  - fetch-user.ts

Variables:
- camelCase
- Descriptive names only
- No abbreviations
- Bad: res, tmp, data2
- Good: userResponse, requestTimeoutMs

Constants:
- SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
- Declared at the top of the file

Functions:
- verbNoun format
- Must describe intent
- Bad: handle, process, doThing
- Good: fetchUserProfile, validateLoginForm

Types / Interfaces / Enums:
- PascalCase
- No I-prefix
- Bad: IUser, user_type
- Good: User, AuthStatus

Booleans:
- Must start with is / has / can / should
- Bad: loggedIn
- Good: isLoggedIn

## src/routes/** (Pages & Layouts)

Rules:
- Routes must be thin
- No business logic
- No direct API calls except via lib/

Allowed:
- Calling lib functions
- Wiring data to UI
- Minimal orchestration

Forbidden:
- Data transformation logic
- Complex conditionals
- Shared state definitions

Naming:
- loadUserPageData
- submitLoginAction

## src/lib/api/** (Network Layer)

Rules:
- One API domain per file
- No UI logic
- No store access
- No side effects outside requests

Naming:
- Files: fetch-user.ts, update-profile.ts
- Functions must start with:
  - fetch
  - create
  - update
  - delete

Error Handling:
- Do not throw raw errors
- Normalize errors before returning
- API functions must return typed results or typed errors

## src/lib/stores/** (State Management)

Rules:
- One store per file
- State must be explicitly typed
- No derived logic inside components

Naming:
- Store file: auth-store.ts
- Store creator: createAuthStore
- Store instance: authStore

## src/lib/utils/** (Utilities)

Rules:
- Pure functions only
- No stores
- No API calls
- No browser APIs unless explicitly required

Naming:
- formatDate
- calculateChecksum
- parseJwtPayload

## src/lib/types/** (Shared Types)

Rules:
- Types only
- No logic
- No runtime imports

Naming:
- One domain per file
- user.types.ts
- auth.types.ts

## src/components/** (UI Components)

Rules:
- No business logic
- No API calls
- Minimal local state
- Props must be explicitly typed

Naming:
- Components: PascalCase.svelte
- Props: camelCase
- Event handlers: handleClick, handleSubmit

## Error Handling (Client-Side Strict)

- DO NOT use console.log, console.error, console.warn in client code
- Browser console must stay clean in production
- Errors must be:
  - handled silently
  - shown via UI state
  - reported via server-side logging or error reporting services

Allowed:
- Returning normalized error objects
- Updating error stores
- Showing user-safe messages

Forbidden:
- Logging errors to Chrome DevTools
- Exposing stack traces to users
- Throwing uncaught errors in UI code

## Async & Performance

- Use async/await consistently
- Prefer Promise.all for parallel work
- Abort in-flight requests on unmount using AbortController
- Lazy-load routes and heavy components

## Absolute Rules (No Exceptions)

- No any
- No unused imports
- No circular dependencies
- No module-scope side effects
- No vague naming
- No client-side console logging

## Goal

The codebase must remain:
- Maintainable
- Type-safe
- Scalable
- Readable
- Production-ready
